text: Former church, now a woodworking shop, Van Zandt, Washington, 2020 Van Zandt is an unincorporated community in Whatcom County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Van Zandt was established in 1892, and remained in operation until 1955. J. M. Van Zandt, an early postmaster, gave the community his name. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Whatcom County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Van Zandt, Washington
